      <P class=3D"style207"><span class=3D"style224"><STRONG><hr>
      </STRONG></span><span class=3D"style246">The Cost of Your Product/Ser=
vice...... and the Cost of Poor Sales Performance?</span>      <p class=3D"=
style78">It is easy to see the cost of price slashing that quickly erodes y=
our margins. The cost of salaries, advertising and marketing, product or se=
rvice delivery and everything else that goes into selling your product all =
remain the same, However your margins or bottom line decrease when you are =
ineffective in dealing with the pricing objection. In addition to not effec=
tively dealing with the pricing objection there is something else we need t=
o keep in mind. Sales is unique in that it is really the only occupation th=
at spends most of its time focused on getting in to see the "decision-maker=
". The decision-maker is the one who has the least amount of time!</p>
      <p class=3D"style78">Once they make that ultimate contact sales peopl=
e begin to pitch, present and demonstrate their features and benefits, in o=
ther words they provide the customer with a lot of intellect. Unfortunately=
, this method of presentation often turns decision-makers into procrastinat=
ors. <o:p></O:P></p>
